text: Toronto is an unincorporated community in Camden County, in the U.S. state of Missouri. ==History== A post office called Toronto was established in 1856, and remained in operation until 1942. The community was named after Toronto, Ontario, Canada, the native home of a share of the first settlers. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Camden County, Missouri Category:Unincorporated communities in Missouri
title: Toronto, Missouri
